    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/239">Otto</persName> divina favente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si petitionibus fidelium
                        nostrorum iustis et rationabilibus divini cultus amore favemus et
                        necessariis proclamationibus aures pietatis nostre accomodamus, et apud deum
                        veniam promereri et nostri imperii vires non ambigimus roborari. Quapropter
                        omnium sancte dei ecclesie nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum
                        comperiat industria, quia <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Gotefredus"
                                >Gottefredus</name></persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/138"
                            key="#Villas #Curtes #Fisheries #Coloni/tenants #Operae #Castle #Markets #Decima #Public_exactions #Census #Angaria #Profits_of_justice #Immunity #Districtio #Inquisitio #Churches #Baptismal_churches #Freeborn #Slave #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius #Arimannus"
                            >sancte <placeName ref="#places/67">Lunensis</placeName>
                            ecclesie</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> ad nostram noticiam venit proclamando de
                        pluribus sue ecclesie iniustis oppressionibus a seculari et publica
                        potestate temere illatis, ita ut, cuntempto amore et timore dei et abiecta a
                        predecessoribus nostris interdicta, <rs
                            key="#Profits_of_justice #Districtio">districtiones</rs> in <rs
                            key="#Slave">servos et ancillas</rs> faciant pertinentes ad eandem
                        ecclesiam, <rs key="#Public_exactions">tributa</rs> ab eis <rs
                            key="#Angaria">angarias</rs> et <rs key="#Operae">opera</rs>
                        <rs key="#Census">census</rs> et donaria exigant, quod deo odibile
                        certissime credimus, quia tales violentias apud Christianos non debere fieri
                        procul dubio scimus. Ideoque omnium fidelium nostrorum tam religiosorum <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcoporum</rs> quam devotorum <rs key="#Count"
                            >comitum</rs> noverit industria, predictas superstitiones et importunas
                        violentias quas quidam nefario ausu res eiusdem ecclesie invadendo
                        committunt, funditus ab hodierno die et deinceps a sancta Lunensis ecclesia
                        nullus <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> vel <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> seu
                        quelibet iudiciarie potestatis persona <rs key="#Immunity">tam in civitate
                            quam in <rs key="#Plebs">plebibus</rs> nec non seu in titulis aliisque
                                <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiis</rs> ac <rs key="#Houses">domibus</rs>
                            sive rusticis possessionibus ad eandem sanctam ecclesiam pertinentibus
                                <rs key="#Assembly">placita</rs> tenere, <rs key="#Coloni/tenants"
                                >massarios et collonos</rs>
                            <rs key="#Freeborn">liberos</rs> et <rs key="#Slave">servos</rs>
                            distringere pignorare angariare, census et redibitiones et donaria
                            aliqua exigere presumat</rs>, sed concti homines residentes supra
                        predictas res sancte Lunensis ecclesie quos legalis coactio exigat querere
                        ad placitum, per <rs key="#Contractors #Clergy/religious_persons"
                            >patronum</rs> seu <rs key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"
                            >advocatum</rs> suum ad placita ducantur, ut legalis diffinitio finem
                        imponat. Hec iam in omnibus <rs key="#Freeborn">liberis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Arimannus">herimanis</rs> prefate ecclesie filiis et in eadem <rs
                            key="#Dioecesis">diocesi</rs> commanentibus <rs key="#Coloni/tenants"
                            >massariis et collonis</rs> observari omnimodis iubemus, videlicet ut ab
                        eis nec donaria aut redibitiones nec pignorationes vel iniuste districtiones
                        exigantur, verum uniuscuiusque legalis censura exigat ut a patrono suo
                        unusquisque ad placitum ducatur, ne pignorationis occasio aditum rapine
                        predatoribus in aliquo prestet. Insuper et concedimus confirmamus et
                        corroboramus et omnino transfundimus cuncta que per cartarum paginam a
                        ceteris deum timentibus collata sunt predicte ecclesie seu que
                        diligentissima perquisitione et veterum preceptorum antiqua attestatione ex
                        parte regni nostri eidem prefate ecclesie pertinere et per plurima annorum
                        curricula ab ea detineri cognovimus. Confirmamus etiam in <geogName
                            ref="#estates/161" key="#Curtes #Comitatus"><rs key="#Comitatus"
                                >comitatu</rs>
                            <placeName ref="#places/53" key="#Curtes"
                            >Parmensi</placeName></geogName>
                        <rs key="#Curtes">corticellam</rs> que dicitur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2403"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Linariclum</placeName></geogName>, et <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1415">sancti Georgii</orgName> positam in loco
                        qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/1841" key="#Churches"
                            >Uariano</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis, atque ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >sancti Terentii</orgName> in loco qui dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/1842" key="#Churches">Carrellia</placeName>, et aliam
                        ecclesiam in loco qui dicitur <placeName key="#Churches"
                            >Uuipilia</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis, <rs key="#Markets"
                            >mercatum</rs> etiam in <rs key="#Baptismal_churches">plebe</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Markets #Baptismal_churches"
                            >sancti Cassiani</orgName> et alium in plebe <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Markets #Baptismal_churches"
                            >sancti Stephani</orgName> nec non et omnes plebes et
                        cortes, <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants #Castle #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            ref="#places/1838"><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants #Castle #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                                >Ameliam</geogName></placeName> videlicet cum <rs
                            key="#Castle">castello</rs> et curte una, cum omnibus rebus mobilibus et
                        immobilibus <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">collonis et collonabus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Aldius">aldiis et aldiabus</rs>, cun <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">venationibus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs> infra ipsius episcopatus terram
                        habentibus et [confl]uentibus, nominative etiam <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#places/1840"><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                ref="#estates/2405">Campilia</geogName></placeName> cum piscatione
                        et venatione sua. Volumus etiam ut <rs key="#Inquisitio">per liberos homines
                            inquisitio facta sit</rs> de rebus predicte ecclesie que ab ea iniuste
                        abstracte sunt; quod infra XL et XXX annos tenuit, teneat in vestituram et
                        inantea. Pretera confirmamus <rs key="#Decima">decimam</rs> VI <rs
                            key="#Villas">villarum</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Villas #Decima"><placeName key="#Villas #Decima"
                                >Uuiffula</placeName></geogName>, <geogName key="#Villas #Decima"
                                ><placeName key="#Villas #Decima">Pontula</placeName></geogName>,
                            <geogName key="#Villas #Decima"><placeName key="#Villas #Decima"
                                >Ualeburdulasca</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Decima"><placeName key="#Villas #Decima"
                                >Tenirano</placeName></geogName> et <geogName key="#Villas #Decima"
                            ref="#estates/1424"><placeName key="#Villas #Decima" ref="#places/1839"
                                >Rupinalia</placeName></geogName>, <geogName key="#Villas #Decima"
                                ><placeName key="#Villas #Decima">Caustello</placeName></geogName>
                        quam <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Waldegarius"
                            >Gualcherius</name></persName> sancte Lunensis ecclesie super <persName
                            key="#Abbots"><name ref="Winibaldus">Guinebaldum</name></persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/151">Bobiensis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs> [in] presentia <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/32">Karoli</persName> imperatoris et <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">legatorum sancte sedis
                            apostolice</rs> per iudicium vindicavit. Et ut hec nostra imperialis
                        institutio et promulgata auctoritas nostrumque confirmationis preceptum
                        proprium robor obtineat, iubemus ut, si quis contra hec que in hac pagina
                        continentur, in aliquo agere convictus fuerit, <rs key="#Penalty">C libras
                            auri optimi</rs> componere cogatur, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem
                            camere nostre</rs> et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities"
                            >medietatem pontifici sancte Lunensis ecclesie</rs> qui pro tempore
                        fuerit. Et ut verius credatur diligentiusque ab omnibus imposterum
                        observetur, manus illud nostre inscriptione annotavimus et anulo nostro
                        subter insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Ottonis serenissi- (M.) mi et
                        invictissimi imperatoris augusti. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> advicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petri</name></persName> episcopi et <rs>archicancellarii</rs> recognovi
                        et scripsi. Data XV kal. Aug. Anno dominice incarnationis DCCCCLXXXI, anno
                        regni domni Ottonis secundi XXI, imperii autem eius XIIII, indictione VIII;
                        actum in <placeName>campo Circi</placeName>; feliciter amen. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
